Migrations are applied in their filename order.
In your case `10_delete_initial_users.js` will be executed before the system migrations (*the system migrations will eventually change in the future to have a negative/zero-ed value to avoid the conflict with user migrations*).
For now, it is recommended to use a timestamp value as prefix for your migration file, for example: `1697193097_delete_initial_users.js`.
*You can also use the builtin `./pocketbase migrate create 'delete initial users'` command that will generate a blank template migration file for you.*

